1
00:00:46,299 --> 00:00:48,968
STILL SHINING

2
00:01:03,399 --> 00:01:05,234
You two must have looked
inside the test room.

3
00:01:05,318 --> 00:01:06,444
Did it have a clock?

4
00:01:06,527 --> 00:01:07,445
It didn't.

5
00:01:08,237 --> 00:01:10,448
I'm sure they'll tell you the time,
but just in case,

6
00:01:10,531 --> 00:01:12,742
make sure you two bring watches.

7
00:01:12,825 --> 00:01:16,204
I'll pick you up at 7:00 a.m. tomorrow,
so come to the bus stop.

8
00:01:16,287 --> 00:01:18,664
-Don't be late.
-Okay.

9
00:01:20,083 --> 00:01:21,334
Go to bed early,

10
00:01:21,417 --> 00:01:24,087
make sure you eat breakfast,
and don't forget your packed lunch.

11
00:01:24,170 --> 00:01:26,464
And your exam ID slip. That's crucial.

12
00:01:26,547 --> 00:01:27,548
-Yes, sir.
-Okay.

13
00:01:28,841 --> 00:01:30,426
-Get a good night's sleep.
-Okay.

14
00:01:36,933 --> 00:01:37,850
Hello?

15
00:01:41,145 --> 00:01:43,564
Well, that…

16
00:01:44,148 --> 00:01:45,942
You mean the paperwork?

17
00:01:46,859 --> 00:01:48,945
<i>Let's meet at 6:50 a.m. tomorrow.</i>

18
00:01:49,028 --> 00:01:50,363
If you go in the room…

19
00:01:50,947 --> 00:01:52,281
The second drawer on the right.

20
00:01:52,365 --> 00:01:53,741
<i>Okay. Sleep tight.</i>

21
00:01:54,408 --> 00:01:55,868
It's there? I told you.

22
00:01:55,952 --> 00:01:57,787
Okay, I got it.

23
00:01:58,371 --> 00:02:00,123
Okay, bye.

24
00:02:07,463 --> 00:02:08,756
You didn't have to wait outside.

25
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:10,508
Hello, Mr. Mu.

26
00:02:11,050 --> 00:02:13,052
You've gone above and beyond to help

27
00:02:13,136 --> 00:02:15,763
right up until the day before the exam.

28
00:02:15,847 --> 00:02:18,266
-We're really grateful.
-Not at all.

29
00:02:18,349 --> 00:02:19,642
It's my pleasure.

30
00:02:21,269 --> 00:02:25,231
Sir, Tae-seo needs a wristwatch,
but mine's digital.

31
00:02:25,314 --> 00:02:26,482
Do you have an analog one?

32
00:02:27,733 --> 00:02:30,027
This one's over 40 years old.

33
00:02:30,111 --> 00:02:31,445
It's fine as long as it works.

34
00:02:32,822 --> 00:02:33,781
Is that so?

35
00:02:35,449 --> 00:02:36,576
Give me your hand.

36
00:02:37,326 --> 00:02:38,286
Put it on now,

37
00:02:38,369 --> 00:02:39,412
so you don't forget.

38
00:02:47,753 --> 00:02:50,214
You two did a great job looking after him.

39
00:02:51,382 --> 00:02:53,009
You did far more for him.

40
00:03:44,894 --> 00:03:45,937
<i>Did you sleep well?</i>

41
00:03:46,020 --> 00:03:48,272
Yeah, better than I thought I would.

42
00:03:48,356 --> 00:03:49,982
I thought I'd be too nervous to sleep.

43
00:03:50,566 --> 00:03:53,402
I think knowing you'd be taking
the exam in the next room

44
00:03:53,486 --> 00:03:54,695
made me feel at ease.

45
00:03:57,782 --> 00:03:59,909
Did you wait long? You must've been cold.

46
00:04:00,785 --> 00:04:01,744
I'm hot.

47
00:04:01,827 --> 00:04:04,413
My dad said it's always cold
in Korea on exam day.

48
00:04:07,166 --> 00:04:08,084
I want to wear it.

49
00:04:17,802 --> 00:04:18,844
Like this?

50
00:04:18,928 --> 00:04:19,762
No.

51
00:04:23,474 --> 00:04:26,310
Wrap it round and around,

52
00:04:27,728 --> 00:04:28,729
and then tie it.

53
00:04:39,282 --> 00:04:42,410
My goal is to get into a school
as close to you as possible.

54
00:04:43,286 --> 00:04:45,830
If I can't get into one in Seoul,
then at least one nearby.

55
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:52,086
Please let us both
achieve our goals today.

56
00:04:54,005 --> 00:04:55,006
I think

57
00:04:55,715 --> 00:04:57,300
this will help me do well.

58
00:04:58,467 --> 00:04:59,635
Give me something too.

59
00:04:59,719 --> 00:05:00,636
Anything of yours.

60
00:05:10,021 --> 00:05:10,855
I have something.

61
00:05:13,441 --> 00:05:15,568
YEONWOO HIGH SCHOOL
YEON TAE-SEO

62
00:05:16,193 --> 00:05:17,028
My lucky charm.

63
00:05:19,488 --> 00:05:23,034
EXAM ROOM 6

64
00:05:41,385 --> 00:05:47,308
STILL SHINING

65
00:05:48,684 --> 00:05:51,353
The exam's over!

66
00:05:54,607 --> 00:05:55,608
Am I the only happy one?

67
00:05:59,737 --> 00:06:00,613
It's over!

68
00:06:04,116 --> 00:06:06,410
Tae-seo, let's go see the Hangang River.

69
00:06:06,494 --> 00:06:08,287
We've seen the ocean,
so we need to go there.

70
00:06:08,954 --> 00:06:10,039
But the time…

71
00:06:10,122 --> 00:06:11,248
Come on. We can make it.

72
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:13,793
One second.

73
00:06:21,842 --> 00:06:22,927
I only have 7,000 won.

74
00:06:23,469 --> 00:06:24,386
Let's go next time.

75
00:06:29,183 --> 00:06:31,435
I didn't use my allowance
since I was studying with you.

76
00:06:31,519 --> 00:06:33,771
You helped me save it,
so I should spend it with you.

77
00:06:33,854 --> 00:06:35,356
Come on, let's take the train.

78
00:06:43,364 --> 00:06:44,615
Not the train.

79
00:06:55,042 --> 00:06:57,169
Let's see the river
from Dongseoul Bus Terminal.

80
00:06:57,253 --> 00:06:58,462
Can you see it from there?

81
00:06:58,546 --> 00:07:00,840
Yeah, the Hangang River is close
to Gangbyeon Station.

82
00:07:02,049 --> 00:07:04,301
We'll see the river,
leave from Gangbyeon Station,

83
00:07:04,385 --> 00:07:07,555
take the last train from Cheongnyangni,
and arrive early tomorrow morning.

84
00:07:07,638 --> 00:07:09,014
Why are we taking the train back?

85
00:07:09,557 --> 00:07:12,393
The train takes around six hours…

86
00:07:15,062 --> 00:07:18,357
so we can be together for longer.

87
00:07:20,484 --> 00:07:21,360
Genius.

88
00:07:24,738 --> 00:07:26,699
What can we do with 7,000 won?

89
00:07:28,409 --> 00:07:29,827
Buy me noodles from a tent bar.

90
00:07:29,910 --> 00:07:32,413
My dad said the noodles
in Seoul tent bars are really good.

91
00:07:33,706 --> 00:07:34,540
Okay.

92
00:07:46,302 --> 00:07:47,887
-Want to go there?
-Okay.

93
00:07:49,430 --> 00:07:50,764
Here are your noodles.

94
00:07:50,848 --> 00:07:52,016
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

95
00:08:00,483 --> 00:08:01,942
It's familiar, but it's delicious.

96
00:08:06,989 --> 00:08:08,866
I love noodles.

97
00:08:08,949 --> 00:08:10,868
And every time, my dad would say

98
00:08:10,951 --> 00:08:12,495
that when my mom was pregnant with me,

99
00:08:12,578 --> 00:08:14,121
she'd always crave these noodles.

100
00:08:14,663 --> 00:08:16,790
I'd always wondered what they tasted like.

101
00:08:22,463 --> 00:08:23,672
I know.

102
00:08:23,756 --> 00:08:25,966
I'm always talking
about my mom when I come to Seoul.

103
00:08:26,050 --> 00:08:27,259
I don't miss her though.

104
00:08:30,596 --> 00:08:31,430
Does she live here?

105
00:08:32,723 --> 00:08:33,849
No, she lives abroad.

106
00:08:34,850 --> 00:08:36,143
But I don't know where.

107
00:08:36,227 --> 00:08:37,561
I never asked.

108
00:08:39,230 --> 00:08:41,065
I'm sure she's doing well somewhere.

109
00:08:42,566 --> 00:08:44,693
Somewhere that has nothing to do with me.

110
00:08:49,532 --> 00:08:51,575
We can take the subway
at 10:00 p.m., so don't rush.

111
00:08:52,701 --> 00:08:53,953
What about the Hangang River?

112
00:08:54,995 --> 00:08:56,580
You can see it from the station.

113
00:08:56,664 --> 00:08:57,957
Not from the station.

114
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,833
I want to see it up close.

115
00:09:04,713 --> 00:09:05,631
We better eat quickly.

116
00:09:12,805 --> 00:09:14,848
The Hangang River's right in front of me.

117
00:09:14,932 --> 00:09:15,933
This is my first time.

118
00:09:16,016 --> 00:09:16,892
Me too.

119
00:09:17,685 --> 00:09:19,853
-Let's get a bit closer.
-Wait.

120
00:09:21,814 --> 00:09:22,856
You're…

121
00:09:23,607 --> 00:09:24,525
going to be cold.

122
00:09:26,402 --> 00:09:27,319
Wrap it round…

123
00:09:28,988 --> 00:09:29,989
and around,

124
00:09:30,573 --> 00:09:31,448
and then tie it.

125
00:09:34,910 --> 00:09:36,870
What about you? Aren't you cold?

126
00:09:36,954 --> 00:09:37,788
I can…

127
00:09:39,707 --> 00:09:40,666
just wear this.

128
00:09:54,513 --> 00:09:55,556
It's a historic day.

129
00:09:55,639 --> 00:09:57,600
I saw both the ocean
and the Hangang River.

130
00:09:58,851 --> 00:10:00,311
I have to remember this day.

131
00:10:07,443 --> 00:10:08,277
Yeon Tae-seo.

132
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:10,404
I just found my dream.

133
00:10:10,487 --> 00:10:11,447
Living on my own.

134
00:10:12,072 --> 00:10:13,407
Living away from my dad.

135
00:10:13,490 --> 00:10:15,993
This counts as a dream

136
00:10:16,076 --> 00:10:18,495
because it's only possible
if my dad gets better.

137
00:10:18,579 --> 00:10:20,998
If he's not doing well,
I can't even consider it.

138
00:10:21,081 --> 00:10:24,460
My dream is for my dad to get well
so I can become independent.

139
00:10:26,462 --> 00:10:27,296
How about you?

140
00:10:28,380 --> 00:10:29,381
Me?

141
00:10:30,132 --> 00:10:31,258
Mine is…

142
00:10:34,178 --> 00:10:36,388
If yours is independence,
mine is self-reliance.

143
00:10:37,056 --> 00:10:38,307
I don't have a "from."

144
00:10:39,725 --> 00:10:41,060
That's really amazing.

145
00:10:41,810 --> 00:10:42,645
What do you mean?

146
00:10:42,728 --> 00:10:45,898
Because I know
you'll achieve that like it's nothing.

147
00:10:46,482 --> 00:10:49,234
From what I've seen,
you're good at doing things on your own.

148
00:10:50,486 --> 00:10:52,696
-I am?
-Yeah.

149
00:10:52,780 --> 00:10:54,615
I don't like doing things by myself,

150
00:10:54,698 --> 00:10:56,158
but you're really good at it.

151
00:10:56,241 --> 00:10:58,786
I've never seen you hang out with people.

152
00:10:59,370 --> 00:11:00,663
You're fine on your own.

153
00:11:01,288 --> 00:11:02,498
It's kind of amazing.

154
00:11:03,957 --> 00:11:05,084
Then again,

155
00:11:05,167 --> 00:11:07,461
I bet things will be different
when you go to college.

156
00:11:09,088 --> 00:11:11,632
I wonder what else will change about you.

157
00:11:13,676 --> 00:11:15,511
I doubt anything will change.

158
00:11:20,099 --> 00:11:21,100
Want to go a bit further?

159
00:11:22,851 --> 00:11:24,728
Yeah. Do we have time?

160
00:11:28,774 --> 00:11:30,484
No, we don't.

161
00:11:32,778 --> 00:11:33,612
Let's go.

162
00:11:34,696 --> 00:11:35,531
We have to go.

163
00:11:35,614 --> 00:11:36,907
Come on, we'll be late.

164
00:11:49,002 --> 00:11:50,838
We walked way too far to see the river.

165
00:11:54,174 --> 00:11:55,175
Hold on.

166
00:11:56,301 --> 00:11:57,302
Gosh, I'm exhausted.

167
00:11:57,845 --> 00:11:59,012
I burned off all the noodles.

168
00:12:02,433 --> 00:12:03,600
Come on, we're late.

169
00:12:07,229 --> 00:12:08,230
Let's go.

170
00:12:14,319 --> 00:12:15,320
Run.

171
00:12:40,262 --> 00:12:43,807
<i>This morning at the bus stop,</i>

172
00:12:44,349 --> 00:12:45,851
<i>I was watching you arrive.</i>

173
00:13:04,036 --> 00:13:05,579
<i>Where we'll be,</i>

174
00:13:06,497 --> 00:13:07,539
<i>what we'll be doing,</i>

175
00:13:08,332 --> 00:13:09,458
<i>and with whom.</i>

176
00:13:11,001 --> 00:13:14,880
<i>I wondered which of these three</i>
<i>would be decided by today's exam.</i>

177
00:13:17,090 --> 00:13:17,925
<i>Then,</i>

178
00:13:18,717 --> 00:13:21,970
<i>could this be the last time</i>

179
00:13:22,554 --> 00:13:24,014
<i>we're headed</i>

180
00:13:25,641 --> 00:13:26,975
<i>in the same direction?</i>

181
00:13:30,437 --> 00:13:32,064
It's not certain yet,

182
00:13:32,981 --> 00:13:35,817
but things will change
when we're at different schools, right?

183
00:13:37,611 --> 00:13:38,654
No.

184
00:13:39,363 --> 00:13:42,699
Distance only mattered
when text messages didn't exist.

185
00:13:45,452 --> 00:13:47,538
If we can still send texts,

186
00:13:48,205 --> 00:13:49,414
no place is too far.

187
00:13:50,332 --> 00:13:51,708
We can text from anywhere.

188
00:13:51,792 --> 00:13:53,085
Exactly.

189
00:13:54,253 --> 00:13:55,629
Texting works everywhere.

190
00:13:56,255 --> 00:13:57,798
Even Yeonwoo has great service.

191
00:13:59,049 --> 00:14:02,761
Would texting not work somewhere
really remote in another country?

192
00:14:02,844 --> 00:14:04,596
Unless we're in different worlds,

193
00:14:06,181 --> 00:14:07,391
we can still text.

194
00:14:08,976 --> 00:14:10,143
Different worlds…

195
00:14:12,271 --> 00:14:13,522
That's my mom and me.

196
00:14:16,984 --> 00:14:17,859
Same.

197
00:14:22,072 --> 00:14:24,491
There's something that only applies to us.

198
00:14:26,201 --> 00:14:27,536
Because it's you and me.

199
00:14:29,621 --> 00:14:34,501
You and I are going to try really hard
to spend time together.

200
00:14:36,378 --> 00:14:38,171
We'll make every effort.

201
00:14:42,676 --> 00:14:44,678
You like me that much?

202
00:14:46,054 --> 00:14:47,055
Of course.

203
00:14:47,639 --> 00:14:49,641
If I hadn't been this sure,

204
00:14:51,685 --> 00:14:53,061
I wouldn't have even tried.

205
00:14:54,354 --> 00:14:55,397
Even when I had…

206
00:14:57,900 --> 00:15:00,986
no room in my life to like someone,
these feelings still grew.

207
00:16:45,465 --> 00:16:46,758
I want to be with you.

208
00:17:09,239 --> 00:17:10,782
-Shall we?
-Yeah.

209
00:17:11,283 --> 00:17:12,284
Shall we?

210
00:18:02,459 --> 00:18:03,585
Where should I go?

211
00:18:06,505 --> 00:18:07,589
Over there?

212
00:19:19,995 --> 00:19:21,788
Your room is nice.

213
00:19:22,706 --> 00:19:23,665
Yeah.

214
00:19:41,183 --> 00:19:42,017
Let me…

215
00:19:42,601 --> 00:19:43,602
I can do it.

216
00:20:55,173 --> 00:20:56,007
Hold on.

217
00:21:32,002 --> 00:21:33,003
Sorry.

218
00:22:18,381 --> 00:22:19,466
Eun-a, are you home?

219
00:22:27,807 --> 00:22:28,975
Is that your dad?

220
00:22:30,643 --> 00:22:31,728
Eun-a.

221
00:22:31,811 --> 00:22:33,271
Yeah, Dad!

222
00:22:39,444 --> 00:22:40,612
I'm home.

223
00:22:42,113 --> 00:22:43,656
I'm going to wash up and go to bed.

224
00:22:43,740 --> 00:22:45,241
Are you going to school tomorrow?

225
00:22:45,325 --> 00:22:46,868
I have to, but I can go late.

226
00:22:48,453 --> 00:22:49,454
Good night, Dad.

227
00:22:50,371 --> 00:22:51,748
Okay, well done today.

228
00:22:52,290 --> 00:22:53,291
Get some rest.

229
00:22:54,084 --> 00:22:55,293
I'm proud of you, my girl.

230
00:22:56,127 --> 00:22:57,087
Thanks.

231
00:23:13,103 --> 00:23:14,062
Is he gone?

232
00:23:53,059 --> 00:23:54,060
No.

233
00:23:58,690 --> 00:24:01,276
Actually, I have a huge secret.

234
00:24:03,278 --> 00:24:05,780
I was too embarrassed to tell you.

235
00:24:22,005 --> 00:24:23,715
I was so hot I thought I'd die.

236
00:24:24,924 --> 00:24:27,218
I kept thinking about my thermals
as I took off my coat.

237
00:24:27,302 --> 00:24:29,888
It wasn't even that cold today,
but my dad insisted.

238
00:24:32,390 --> 00:24:33,683
This is so embarrassing.

239
00:24:33,766 --> 00:24:36,019
Why did it have to be floral?

240
00:24:38,897 --> 00:24:39,981
What?

241
00:24:41,149 --> 00:24:42,358
I think it's cute.

242
00:25:33,785 --> 00:25:35,870
You've always done well,

243
00:25:35,954 --> 00:25:37,497
so let's just figure out where to go.

244
00:25:37,580 --> 00:25:38,873
Go think about it.

245
00:25:38,957 --> 00:25:40,625
Okay. Thank you.

246
00:25:40,708 --> 00:25:41,668
Off you go.

247
00:25:46,214 --> 00:25:47,340
My gosh.

248
00:26:06,484 --> 00:26:08,861
Mo Eun-a, well done. You did a good job.

249
00:26:09,821 --> 00:26:10,655
Thank you.

250
00:26:11,614 --> 00:26:15,159
You did really well considering
you only started studying half a year ago.

251
00:26:16,160 --> 00:26:16,995
Really.

252
00:26:17,495 --> 00:26:19,163
If you'd started a year earlier,

253
00:26:20,081 --> 00:26:22,000
we could've tried
the regional admissions track.

254
00:26:22,583 --> 00:26:23,584
It's a shame.

255
00:26:25,420 --> 00:26:26,963
Now, let's see.

256
00:27:03,124 --> 00:27:08,880
DECEMBER

257
00:27:16,554 --> 00:27:18,431
DEPARTMENT OF MECHANICAL ENGINEERING

258
00:27:18,514 --> 00:27:20,016
YOUR APPLICATION HAS BEEN SUBMITTED

259
00:27:20,099 --> 00:27:21,309
All done.

260
00:27:21,392 --> 00:27:23,561
I feel so glad
to have it submitted quickly.

261
00:27:24,395 --> 00:27:27,148
The results come out on February 4th, so…

262
00:27:27,231 --> 00:27:28,983
Just kick back and relax.

263
00:27:39,994 --> 00:27:41,788
Yeah, it's beautiful.

264
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:01,682
Eun-a.

265
00:28:06,979 --> 00:28:08,981
Merry early Christmas.

266
00:28:22,620 --> 00:28:23,621
The guests are here.

267
00:28:23,704 --> 00:28:25,373
Yeah, I'm all done.

268
00:28:27,041 --> 00:28:29,794
Thanks to your help,
I'm officially on the concierge team now.

269
00:28:29,877 --> 00:28:30,753
Thank you so much.

270
00:28:31,754 --> 00:28:34,507
I heard you specifically asked
to work with only me.

271
00:28:35,550 --> 00:28:36,551
Because you're good.

272
00:28:40,304 --> 00:28:43,224
I think having to deal with
a different person each time

273
00:28:43,891 --> 00:28:45,560
bothers Seon-gyu a bit.

274
00:28:45,643 --> 00:28:47,186
He seemed to struggle with it.

275
00:28:48,229 --> 00:28:49,856
So it's a win-win.

276
00:28:52,358 --> 00:28:54,110
You haven't had dinner yet, right?

277
00:28:54,193 --> 00:28:57,655
You eat this one,
and please take the other one to Eun-a.

278
00:28:59,532 --> 00:29:02,869
Whenever the guests are here,
she never comes out of her room.

279
00:29:08,332 --> 00:29:10,209
How did you feel when you submitted it?

280
00:29:10,293 --> 00:29:13,796
Mr. Mu did it for me.
He clicked the "Submit" button too.

281
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:15,047
He clicked it for you?

282
00:29:15,715 --> 00:29:17,508
I didn't ask him to,

283
00:29:17,592 --> 00:29:19,302
but it was just easier for him to do it.

284
00:29:20,970 --> 00:29:22,930
I'd be too nervous to click it myself.

285
00:29:25,558 --> 00:29:28,352
Do adults always have to deal
with stressful things like this?

286
00:29:29,103 --> 00:29:31,522
Why am I always so nervous and scared?

287
00:30:06,015 --> 00:30:07,683
MY APPLICATIONS

288
00:30:15,817 --> 00:30:18,402
If you're done, I'll click it now.
I'm going to submit it.

289
00:30:18,486 --> 00:30:20,279
Mr. Mu, wait.

290
00:30:20,363 --> 00:30:23,241
-No, you've done more than enough.
-Please just wait.

291
00:30:23,324 --> 00:30:25,493
-I can't wait anymore.
-Wait, hold on!

292
00:30:25,576 --> 00:30:27,161
It's Christmas today.

293
00:30:27,245 --> 00:30:28,746
Can I just pray one time?

294
00:30:32,708 --> 00:30:33,960
I should get up to do it.

295
00:30:34,961 --> 00:30:36,045
It's okay. Just pray.

296
00:30:36,128 --> 00:30:38,506
-This gave me a bad feeling.
-Go on, just pray.

297
00:30:42,301 --> 00:30:44,262
Hopefully, we can make it home today.

298
00:30:46,764 --> 00:30:48,599
Dear Santa,
I really want to go to college.

299
00:30:48,683 --> 00:30:51,686
JANUARY

300
00:31:07,493 --> 00:31:08,953
Oh, my god!

301
00:31:10,037 --> 00:31:11,372
Why are you hiding in the corner?

302
00:31:11,956 --> 00:31:12,957
It's so dark.

303
00:31:13,916 --> 00:31:15,585
-You should've turned the lights on.
-No…

304
00:31:17,253 --> 00:31:18,462
I'm fine.

305
00:31:24,510 --> 00:31:25,636
Please come over here.

306
00:31:51,162 --> 00:31:53,915
One thing's for sure.
We always have plenty to eat at our house.

307
00:31:55,333 --> 00:31:56,500
Enjoy your meal.

308
00:31:58,669 --> 00:32:00,796
We need the one you just swiped tonight,

309
00:32:02,340 --> 00:32:03,591
so take any of these instead.

310
00:32:05,509 --> 00:32:06,510
Okay.

311
00:32:39,460 --> 00:32:40,920
Happy New Year.

312
00:33:26,340 --> 00:33:28,509
My first day as a 20-year-old
with Yeon Tae-seo.

313
00:33:34,181 --> 00:33:35,224
We don't have any glasses.

314
00:33:55,411 --> 00:33:56,245
It's sweet.

315
00:34:10,843 --> 00:34:11,969
It's pretty tasty.

316
00:34:15,639 --> 00:34:16,640
It's not alcohol.

317
00:34:16,724 --> 00:34:18,100
It is alcohol.

318
00:34:52,843 --> 00:34:54,095
Let's go.

319
00:35:26,669 --> 00:35:27,920
Eun-a!

320
00:35:29,922 --> 00:35:30,923
Be quiet.

321
00:35:39,014 --> 00:35:44,478
FEBRUARY

322
00:35:45,980 --> 00:35:48,691
All right, shall we toast?

323
00:35:50,317 --> 00:35:51,902
Congratulations.

324
00:35:52,862 --> 00:35:56,740
He made it to Hanguk National University
from this tiny village. Congratulations.

325
00:35:56,824 --> 00:35:58,868
You're too kind.

326
00:35:58,951 --> 00:36:01,078
It's all thanks to Mr. Mu here.

327
00:36:01,162 --> 00:36:03,414
I didn't do much.

328
00:36:03,497 --> 00:36:05,166
He achieved it all on his own.

329
00:36:05,249 --> 00:36:07,585
So did Mr. Mo's daughter not get in?

330
00:36:07,668 --> 00:36:09,044
No, she's still waiting.

331
00:36:09,128 --> 00:36:10,963
There's a first round of results,

332
00:36:11,046 --> 00:36:13,549
then a second, and even a third.

333
00:36:13,632 --> 00:36:15,259
The results come out in batches.

334
00:36:15,342 --> 00:36:17,386
So it's a little complicated.

335
00:36:17,469 --> 00:36:19,471
Gosh, you didn't have to.

336
00:36:19,555 --> 00:36:21,265
Have some of this, Mr. Mu.

337
00:36:21,348 --> 00:36:22,600
-Congratulations.
-Great job.

338
00:36:22,683 --> 00:36:24,059
Thank you.

339
00:36:24,143 --> 00:36:25,936
So, Mr. Mu.

340
00:36:26,020 --> 00:36:28,355
Explain it properly so I can understand.

341
00:36:28,439 --> 00:36:31,400
Well, there is
an additional enrollment period,

342
00:36:31,483 --> 00:36:35,988
and the results don't finish
coming out until late February.

343
00:36:36,071 --> 00:36:37,948
What on earth does that mean?

344
00:36:38,032 --> 00:36:40,784
It must be killing Eun-a
to wait for the results.

345
00:36:42,161 --> 00:36:43,037
Right.

346
00:36:49,501 --> 00:36:50,628
This is my first time.

347
00:36:51,545 --> 00:36:52,546
On the Sea Train?

348
00:36:53,714 --> 00:36:54,798
THIS IS THE SEA TRAIN

349
00:36:54,882 --> 00:36:58,385
It only runs during the day
and follows the coastline.

350
00:36:58,469 --> 00:37:01,472
It takes an hour and 40 minutes
from Gangneung to Samcheok,

351
00:37:01,555 --> 00:37:03,140
so if we go there and come back…

352
00:37:03,224 --> 00:37:05,893
We can be together
for around three and a half hours.

353
00:37:06,644 --> 00:37:07,645
Yeah.

354
00:37:11,357 --> 00:37:12,733
When I was little,

355
00:37:13,692 --> 00:37:15,778
my mom worked here for a bit.

356
00:37:17,029 --> 00:37:19,281
I wanted to become
a Sea Train driver back then.

357
00:37:20,491 --> 00:37:22,284
I guess it looked kind of cool.

358
00:37:25,496 --> 00:37:26,830
That's nice.

359
00:37:29,375 --> 00:37:31,418
What did you want to tell me
all the way out here?

360
00:37:38,592 --> 00:37:40,803
I have to go to Seoul soon.

361
00:37:42,471 --> 00:37:45,641
When I was living in Seoul,
I had a friend called Hyeong-seok.

362
00:37:45,724 --> 00:37:47,393
And his dad runs a study center.

363
00:37:48,644 --> 00:37:51,647
He let me use it for free
and helped me out a lot.

364
00:37:53,023 --> 00:37:55,401
He asked if I could do
some tutoring starting in February.

365
00:37:56,318 --> 00:37:57,820
I'd been putting it off,

366
00:37:58,904 --> 00:38:01,240
but I think I really have to go now.

367
00:38:05,744 --> 00:38:06,912
Right.

368
00:38:08,998 --> 00:38:09,832
You should go.

369
00:38:11,292 --> 00:38:12,543
And your entrance ceremony?

370
00:38:12,626 --> 00:38:14,086
Is Hui-seo joining you later?

371
00:38:14,670 --> 00:38:16,046
He can't go.

372
00:38:16,130 --> 00:38:17,840
He can't do long journeys yet.

373
00:38:18,382 --> 00:38:19,591
He must be upset.

374
00:38:21,176 --> 00:38:22,303
Do you have a place to stay?

375
00:38:22,386 --> 00:38:24,930
Yeah, the study center office has a bed.

376
00:38:25,014 --> 00:38:27,057
How can you sleep in an office?
(Watch on www,kisskh,la to support Admin)

377
00:38:29,268 --> 00:38:30,352
That's so sad.

378
00:38:32,104 --> 00:38:33,355
That's nothing.

379
00:38:35,024 --> 00:38:36,942
You must be more sad
waiting for your results.

380
00:38:39,695 --> 00:38:40,571
Me? Well…

381
00:38:41,238 --> 00:38:43,324
One of the three schools I applied to

382
00:38:43,907 --> 00:38:45,701
is at least close to you,

383
00:38:46,410 --> 00:38:48,454
but my chances of getting in are low.

384
00:38:48,537 --> 00:38:51,206
One is halfway between
here and Seoul, but it's not certain.

385
00:38:51,290 --> 00:38:53,542
The last one is in Gangneung.

386
00:38:54,960 --> 00:38:58,047
Mr. Mu said it's a good school,
and the program is good there.

387
00:38:59,256 --> 00:39:00,132
But…

388
00:39:01,342 --> 00:39:03,052
it's really far from you.

389
00:39:03,677 --> 00:39:07,848
Having to wait for over a month
is making me anxious and uncertain.

390
00:39:08,474 --> 00:39:10,309
It's been dragging on for so long

391
00:39:10,392 --> 00:39:12,353
that I can't believe
February is already ending.

392
00:39:12,895 --> 00:39:14,104
It feels endless.

393
00:39:23,530 --> 00:39:25,032
It's definitely going to end.

394
00:39:27,242 --> 00:39:28,952
I hope so.

395
00:39:37,336 --> 00:39:39,505
An end that really feels like one.

396
00:39:40,631 --> 00:39:42,716
I hope it's a clean end.

397
00:40:08,992 --> 00:40:09,952
Wait.

398
00:40:14,289 --> 00:40:16,417
This isn't much, but take it.

399
00:40:16,500 --> 00:40:18,001
I'm fine. I have money.

400
00:40:18,085 --> 00:40:19,795
Buy yourself something to wear.

401
00:40:21,463 --> 00:40:23,132
Your grandma seemed to feel bad

402
00:40:23,215 --> 00:40:25,884
we couldn't buy you something to wear

403
00:40:25,968 --> 00:40:28,053
to your entrance ceremony.

404
00:40:29,304 --> 00:40:31,390
We can't afford to buy you a suit,

405
00:40:31,473 --> 00:40:34,893
but at least buy yourself a coat.

406
00:40:34,977 --> 00:40:36,728
Something that's nice and formal.

407
00:40:37,479 --> 00:40:39,857
You'll need to dress up
quite often while in the city.

408
00:40:39,940 --> 00:40:42,067
Here. Buy one for yourself.

409
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:44,528
Thank you.

410
00:40:46,822 --> 00:40:50,075
From scholarships to tutoring,
you're doing everything on your own.

411
00:40:50,159 --> 00:40:51,660
We feel terrible.

412
00:40:55,080 --> 00:40:55,998
I'll visit often.

413
00:40:57,332 --> 00:41:00,210
There's no need. You should be studying.
You'll only waste money.

414
00:41:01,587 --> 00:41:03,255
Just make sure you call Hui-seo.

415
00:41:06,341 --> 00:41:09,136
I thought he'd be grumpy
about missing your entrance ceremony,

416
00:41:09,845 --> 00:41:10,888
but he's been quiet.

417
00:41:15,684 --> 00:41:19,521
At least the ceremony doesn't fall
on the same day as your parents' memorial.

418
00:41:20,731 --> 00:41:22,107
It's the first one.

419
00:41:29,531 --> 00:41:31,325
I'll go pay my respects.

420
00:41:32,284 --> 00:41:33,619
Stay at home with Hui-seo.

421
00:41:38,790 --> 00:41:39,750
All right.

422
00:41:40,667 --> 00:41:41,960
Go on, then.

423
00:41:42,878 --> 00:41:43,712
Okay.

424
00:41:50,385 --> 00:41:56,183
WAITING AREA (TICKETS)

425
00:41:59,436 --> 00:42:02,272
<i>Are you taking the express bus to Seoul?</i>

426
00:42:03,690 --> 00:42:04,525
Eun-a.

427
00:42:07,736 --> 00:42:10,322
I was waiting right here.

428
00:42:10,405 --> 00:42:12,407
I thought you'd be taking the train.

429
00:42:12,491 --> 00:42:13,450
I'm such a klutz.

430
00:42:15,160 --> 00:42:16,370
I just…

431
00:42:16,453 --> 00:42:19,456
I know you told me not to,
but I'd feel bad if I didn't see you off.

432
00:42:19,540 --> 00:42:22,709
I'll take you there.
I bought two tickets, so we can just go.

433
00:42:22,793 --> 00:42:23,919
Don't be ridiculous.

434
00:42:37,558 --> 00:42:39,810
How can you make me let you go home alone?

435
00:42:40,686 --> 00:42:41,853
You can let it happen today.

436
00:42:48,402 --> 00:42:49,820
Seriously, it's fine.

437
00:42:53,115 --> 00:42:54,533
Let's get off at the next stop.

438
00:42:55,534 --> 00:42:58,620
I can't bear to watch you go back alone.
I'll take you home and…

439
00:42:58,704 --> 00:43:00,247
So you can go alone, but I can't?

440
00:43:01,915 --> 00:43:03,750
That's nonsense. It's fine.

441
00:43:06,962 --> 00:43:08,630
It's already been an hour.

442
00:43:08,714 --> 00:43:10,132
We don't have time.

443
00:43:10,215 --> 00:43:11,967
How long are you going to keep this up?

444
00:43:22,769 --> 00:43:25,063
LOG IN

445
00:43:28,108 --> 00:43:30,277
PLAYLIST

446
00:43:32,738 --> 00:43:33,655
This is my account.

447
00:43:34,573 --> 00:43:38,577
If I'm using it, it'll say,
"Currently streaming."

448
00:43:39,328 --> 00:43:41,747
We can use it together.
We'll listen to it at the same time.

449
00:43:42,414 --> 00:43:43,415
Then,

450
00:43:44,458 --> 00:43:46,710
it'll feel like we're together.

451
00:43:48,837 --> 00:43:50,714
It'll feel like we're together.

452
00:43:50,797 --> 00:43:51,882
Feeling like we're together

453
00:43:53,258 --> 00:43:54,426
counts as being together.

454
00:43:58,305 --> 00:43:59,306
I like that.

455
00:43:59,973 --> 00:44:01,433
What else is there

456
00:44:01,516 --> 00:44:03,101
to make us feel together?

457
00:44:04,811 --> 00:44:07,481
Sharing the photos we take?
Let's take one now.

458
00:44:11,068 --> 00:44:11,902
Smile.

459
00:44:19,826 --> 00:44:22,162
Sir, how long will it take?

460
00:44:22,245 --> 00:44:23,163
One hour.

461
00:44:23,246 --> 00:44:24,081
What?

462
00:44:27,959 --> 00:44:30,545
You should go.
Let's part here. It's your first lesson.

463
00:44:31,463 --> 00:44:32,422
Eun-a.

464
00:44:35,384 --> 00:44:37,135
This is a lot

465
00:44:37,719 --> 00:44:39,096
harder than I expected.

466
00:44:40,180 --> 00:44:41,431
I can't do it.

467
00:44:42,307 --> 00:44:43,392
I can.

468
00:44:43,475 --> 00:44:46,436
Come on, I can't let you go back alone.

469
00:44:47,896 --> 00:44:50,107
You can. Just like this.

470
00:44:50,190 --> 00:44:53,735
I might end up at a college near you,
or I might not.

471
00:44:54,444 --> 00:44:55,987
I don't know what will happen.

472
00:44:57,781 --> 00:44:59,032
My life is always so uncertain.

473
00:45:00,784 --> 00:45:02,661
Anyway, we'll have to keep doing this,

474
00:45:02,744 --> 00:45:05,247
but if you feel bad or guilty,
it'll be hard to see each other.

475
00:45:09,793 --> 00:45:10,794
This is driving me crazy.

476
00:45:13,964 --> 00:45:15,048
I'll…

477
00:45:15,715 --> 00:45:17,050
I'll do my best for us.

478
00:45:17,884 --> 00:45:18,802
Okay.

479
00:45:25,767 --> 00:45:26,643
Oh, my god.

480
00:45:27,769 --> 00:45:28,770
What?

481
00:45:28,854 --> 00:45:30,355
What is it?

482
00:45:30,439 --> 00:45:31,481
I got in.

483
00:45:32,107 --> 00:45:32,941
What?

484
00:45:33,525 --> 00:45:35,235
GANGNEUNG WONKYEONG UNIVERSITY

485
00:45:36,361 --> 00:45:38,113
No way! I got in!

486
00:45:38,196 --> 00:45:40,615
See? I got in because I was with you!

487
00:45:41,825 --> 00:45:44,077
Oh, my god. But it's a bit far from you.

488
00:45:44,161 --> 00:45:46,455
That's not what matters right now!

489
00:45:47,622 --> 00:45:49,416
Congratulations!

490
00:45:51,168 --> 00:45:54,588
-You really earned this.
-Oh, my god. I'm so happy.

491
00:45:54,671 --> 00:45:58,717
MARCH

492
00:46:44,596 --> 00:46:46,389
-It's nice.
-Nice and clean.

493
00:46:46,473 --> 00:46:47,807
You must be his roommate.

494
00:46:47,891 --> 00:46:49,434
I hope you two get along well.

495
00:46:50,143 --> 00:46:53,271
-The bed here's so soft.
-Sweetie, don't sit there.

496
00:46:53,355 --> 00:46:55,357
Why not? Come try it too, Mom.

497
00:46:58,902 --> 00:46:59,986
This is nice.

498
00:47:12,749 --> 00:47:13,833
Hui-seo…

499
00:47:16,169 --> 00:47:18,338
I'll bring him over when he's a bit older.

500
00:47:26,137 --> 00:47:27,931
Don't worry about him.

501
00:47:31,643 --> 00:47:34,104
And don't worry about Grandma and Grandpa.

502
00:47:38,984 --> 00:47:40,777
I'll take care of everyone.

503
00:47:47,659 --> 00:47:48,660
I almost forgot.

504
00:47:50,912 --> 00:47:53,290
I'm attending the college
you wanted me to go to, Mom.

505
00:48:00,630 --> 00:48:02,716
You would've been so happy
to see me there.

506
00:48:10,724 --> 00:48:11,725
Mom.

507
00:48:14,394 --> 00:48:15,270
Dad.

508
00:48:55,977 --> 00:48:57,771
Can I sit here?

509
00:48:57,854 --> 00:48:58,813
Sure.

510
00:49:09,532 --> 00:49:10,659
I'm Park Na-ri.

511
00:49:12,285 --> 00:49:13,203
I'm Mo Eun-a.

512
00:49:15,205 --> 00:49:17,707
Hey, your student number
is right after mine.

513
00:49:18,416 --> 00:49:19,417
What a coincidence.

514
00:49:21,670 --> 00:49:23,672
I'm from Seoul. You?

515
00:49:23,755 --> 00:49:25,965
I live nearby. Twenty minutes by bus.

516
00:49:26,049 --> 00:49:27,217
-Twenty minutes?
-Yeah.

517
00:49:33,431 --> 00:49:35,100
No way! We have the same elective too?

518
00:49:35,183 --> 00:49:37,352
No way! Come sit here.

519
00:49:44,818 --> 00:49:45,735
What's that?

520
00:49:49,698 --> 00:49:52,409
-Want to pick one?
-They're so cute.

521
00:49:53,618 --> 00:49:54,869
-This one.
-Sure.

522
00:49:54,953 --> 00:49:56,663
-Here.
-Thanks.

523
00:49:57,914 --> 00:50:02,585
This class is called
Creative Engineering Design.

524
00:50:02,669 --> 00:50:04,295
This class will give you the opportunity

525
00:50:04,379 --> 00:50:07,882
to reflect on what lies
beyond the machines.

526
00:50:07,966 --> 00:50:09,926
Great machines are made
when you understand

527
00:50:10,009 --> 00:50:11,261
both their function and value.

528
00:50:11,344 --> 00:50:14,973
What you need for this class
is your mathematical ability

529
00:50:15,056 --> 00:50:16,808
and a brain that's capable of thinking.

530
00:50:16,891 --> 00:50:19,853
The rest you will learn
in this class today.

531
00:50:21,062 --> 00:50:23,314
Did you always want to study
early childhood education?

532
00:50:23,398 --> 00:50:25,692
Yeah, because I like kids.

533
00:50:27,193 --> 00:50:30,655
But teaching's not really for me.
It's not what I expected.

534
00:50:32,532 --> 00:50:35,493
I picked this place for the major,
but now, I'm not so sure.

535
00:50:38,496 --> 00:50:40,540
But it's so nice to see the ocean.

536
00:50:41,875 --> 00:50:43,752
This was worth skipping class.

537
00:50:43,835 --> 00:50:44,669
I know.

538
00:50:46,755 --> 00:50:48,798
I heard the vending machine coffee
was good here.

539
00:50:48,882 --> 00:50:51,259
SORI MARKET

540
00:50:51,342 --> 00:50:52,385
-Want to go?
-Let's go.

541
00:50:55,388 --> 00:50:56,765
<i>We're already really close.</i>

542
00:50:56,848 --> 00:50:58,391
<i>I'm exploring Gangneung thanks to her.</i>

543
00:50:58,475 --> 00:51:00,477
I'll take you around
the next time you're here.

544
00:51:00,560 --> 00:51:01,895
Okay.

545
00:51:04,314 --> 00:51:06,524
<i>I have matching stickers with Na-ri,</i>

546
00:51:06,608 --> 00:51:08,735
<i>but I don't have</i>
<i>anything matching with you.</i>

547
00:51:11,613 --> 00:51:12,864
What do you want to do?

548
00:51:14,657 --> 00:51:16,409
I have a great idea.

549
00:51:16,493 --> 00:51:18,912
What if I make stickers with my drawings?

550
00:51:18,995 --> 00:51:21,206
<i>The same vegetable stickers</i>
<i>for our different classes.</i>

551
00:51:21,790 --> 00:51:22,832
<i>Tell me your classes.</i>

552
00:51:22,916 --> 00:51:24,584
I'll draw something for each one.

553
00:51:24,667 --> 00:51:25,585
I'm really good.

554
00:51:27,337 --> 00:51:28,546
Engineering Mathematics.

555
00:51:29,297 --> 00:51:30,131
<i>Kidney beans.</i>

556
00:51:30,215 --> 00:51:31,800
It's extremely hard to pick them out.

557
00:51:33,551 --> 00:51:36,763
They're hard to pick out? Then…

558
00:51:36,846 --> 00:51:37,972
APRIL

559
00:51:40,600 --> 00:51:42,185
-Kim Na-rae.
-Here.

560
00:51:44,062 --> 00:51:45,230
Kim Ji-ho.

561
00:51:46,731 --> 00:51:47,690
Ji-ho?

562
00:51:49,234 --> 00:51:50,985
-Mo Eun-a.
-Here.

563
00:51:52,612 --> 00:51:53,613
Park Na-ri.

564
00:51:54,739 --> 00:51:56,324
Right, Na-ri took a leave of absence.

565
00:51:57,492 --> 00:52:01,079
It's only been a month,
and someone's already taking time off.

566
00:52:03,122 --> 00:52:05,208
-Park Seo-yeon.
-Here.

567
00:52:05,291 --> 00:52:07,293
-Song A-yeong.
-Here.

568
00:52:18,304 --> 00:52:19,472
PLAYLIST

569
00:52:28,523 --> 00:52:30,525
TAE-SEO

570
00:52:30,608 --> 00:52:32,652
<i>Have the flowers bloomed in Seoul yet?</i>

571
00:52:32,735 --> 00:52:34,237
<i>It's crazy here.</i>

572
00:52:34,320 --> 00:52:36,447
<i>Send me a photo</i>
<i>of the flowers at your school too.</i>

573
00:52:36,531 --> 00:52:40,118
<i>And a selfie of you in front of them too.</i>

574
00:52:44,289 --> 00:52:46,624
<i>I miss you, Tae-seo.</i>

575
00:52:47,792 --> 00:52:49,836
-Hello.
-Hello.

576
00:53:02,765 --> 00:53:05,393
<i>I'll go to school after tutoring</i>
<i>and send it to you.</i>

577
00:53:20,158 --> 00:53:23,494
His tutoring session usually takes
about two hours, so…

578
00:53:25,413 --> 00:53:27,624
<i>Call me when you're done tutoring, okay?</i>

579
00:53:46,309 --> 00:53:47,894
<i>What time do you finish?</i>

580
00:53:48,770 --> 00:53:50,563
WHAT TIME DO YOU FINISH?

581
00:53:58,988 --> 00:54:00,823
<i>I have two tutoring sessions today,</i>

582
00:54:00,907 --> 00:54:02,617
<i>so if I go straight to school after,</i>

583
00:54:02,700 --> 00:54:03,910
<i>it should be around 10:00 p.m.</i>

584
00:54:13,711 --> 00:54:15,421
One ticket to Gangneung, please.

585
00:54:16,172 --> 00:54:17,298
Gangneung?

586
00:54:18,007 --> 00:54:19,217
That'll be 10,600 won.

587
00:54:23,805 --> 00:54:24,639
Dad.

588
00:54:26,766 --> 00:54:28,059
You never ask me to pick you up.

589
00:54:28,810 --> 00:54:29,852
I didn't want to go alone.

590
00:54:30,853 --> 00:54:32,814
Are we going out for a night stroll?

591
00:54:32,897 --> 00:54:35,024
Where should we go? Let's go for sashimi.

592
00:54:36,985 --> 00:54:38,027
I'm tired.

593
00:54:52,709 --> 00:54:54,502
What should we eat?

594
00:54:54,585 --> 00:54:56,587
Is there something you'd like to eat?

595
00:54:57,505 --> 00:54:58,881
I'm up for anything.

596
00:55:00,133 --> 00:55:01,175
Should we ask Eun-a?

597
00:55:01,259 --> 00:55:03,386
Eun-a, is there anything you want to eat?

598
00:55:04,595 --> 00:55:05,763
Eun-a, are you asleep?

599
00:55:07,598 --> 00:55:09,017
She must be really tired.

600
00:55:09,100 --> 00:55:10,685
Just let her sleep.

601
00:55:12,103 --> 00:55:13,855
But we haven't gone out
together in forever.

602
00:55:14,480 --> 00:55:16,441
It'd be nice if we could talk while we go.

603
00:55:16,524 --> 00:55:18,151
<i>I had no idea they'd bloomed so much.</i>

604
00:55:19,610 --> 00:55:20,611
<i>Should I call you?</i>

605
00:55:21,195 --> 00:55:22,321
<i>Is everything okay?</i>

606
00:55:23,656 --> 00:55:26,200
<i>I was just wandering and thought of you.</i>

607
00:55:27,785 --> 00:55:30,788
<i>I can leave in the morning this weekend.</i>

608
00:55:30,872 --> 00:55:31,831
<i>Let's meet up early.</i>

609
00:55:32,790 --> 00:55:34,208
<i>I want to go to Seoul.</i>

610
00:55:35,168 --> 00:55:36,461
<i>It's my turn to go.</i>

611
00:55:36,544 --> 00:55:37,795
<i>I'll come to you.</i>

612
00:55:37,879 --> 00:55:39,380
<i>No, I'll go to you.</i>

613
00:55:39,922 --> 00:55:41,340
<i>Spend your time on yourself.</i>

614
00:55:41,424 --> 00:55:42,759
<i>Don't waste it.</i>

615
00:55:42,842 --> 00:55:44,469
Hello, Hyeong-seok? Yeah.

616
00:55:45,136 --> 00:55:46,929
<i>Your time is precious too.</i>

617
00:55:47,013 --> 00:55:47,972
<i>I'll go to you.</i>

618
00:55:52,643 --> 00:55:54,896
<i>My time right now is just passing by,</i>

619
00:55:55,772 --> 00:55:59,108
<i>but yours is time you need to use</i>
<i>toward your goals.</i>

620
00:55:59,192 --> 00:56:00,318
<i>They're different.</i>

621
00:56:02,612 --> 00:56:04,280
<i>No more dark photos.</i>

622
00:56:05,323 --> 00:56:07,075
<i>I miss you, Tae-seo.</i>

623
00:56:08,242 --> 00:56:09,285
<i>A lot.</i>

624
00:57:05,007 --> 00:57:05,967
This is nice.

625
00:57:06,050 --> 00:57:07,260
Did you miss me?

626
00:57:09,262 --> 00:57:10,096
Of course.

627
00:57:13,391 --> 00:57:20,356
MAY

628
00:57:36,205 --> 00:57:38,583
Every time I take out a cigarette,
you appear.

629
00:57:38,666 --> 00:57:39,709
It's almost scary.

630
00:57:43,796 --> 00:57:45,590
It's fun working at a hotel, isn't it?

631
00:57:46,340 --> 00:57:48,384
I feel good
whenever I see the hotel staff.

632
00:57:48,468 --> 00:57:49,844
Then, try it out.

633
00:57:50,344 --> 00:57:52,638
A lot of local young people
work part-time at our hotel.

634
00:57:52,722 --> 00:57:53,973
Taking time off from school?

635
00:57:55,349 --> 00:57:56,809
What would I be taking time off for?

636
00:57:56,893 --> 00:57:58,686
I don't want to try things out
without a goal

637
00:57:58,769 --> 00:58:00,688
just because everyone else is.

638
00:58:01,814 --> 00:58:02,773
So annoying.

639
00:58:04,609 --> 00:58:06,861
I mean, I know you're in college,

640
00:58:06,944 --> 00:58:09,322
but it's not even vacation time
and you're not at school.

641
00:58:09,405 --> 00:58:12,325
You've been here all day today
and riding your bike the past two days.

642
00:58:13,075 --> 00:58:14,202
You're the first one to ask.

643
00:58:14,785 --> 00:58:16,787
I skipped school all week and slacked off,

644
00:58:16,871 --> 00:58:17,955
but no one's ever asked.

645
00:58:18,039 --> 00:58:19,832
No one from school reached out.

646
00:58:19,916 --> 00:58:22,126
And my dad didn't ask why I wasn't going.

647
00:58:22,960 --> 00:58:24,462
I guess no one really cares.

648
00:58:25,046 --> 00:58:26,631
Thanks for asking.

649
00:58:27,173 --> 00:58:29,675
I'm not going to school
because I don't feel like going.

650
00:58:29,759 --> 00:58:31,677
If you're going to
do college half-heartedly,

651
00:58:31,761 --> 00:58:34,180
you might as well take time off
and try something else.

652
00:58:34,263 --> 00:58:35,640
Don't you want to be independent?

653
00:58:36,265 --> 00:58:37,808
In your current situation,

654
00:58:37,892 --> 00:58:40,144
I doubt your dad would notice
you're not going to school.

655
00:58:40,228 --> 00:58:42,355
If I were you,
I'd be thinking about moving out.

656
00:58:46,359 --> 00:58:48,694
That came out of nowhere. What situation?

657
00:58:48,778 --> 00:58:50,696
Just go pick up your guests.

658
00:58:50,780 --> 00:58:53,866
It was a lunch reservation,
but it'll be dinner time soon.

659
00:58:55,034 --> 00:58:57,537
So-hyeon made
a surprise announcement today.

660
00:58:57,620 --> 00:58:59,622
I can't really ruin the mood.

661
00:59:00,289 --> 00:59:01,582
Announcement?

662
00:59:02,583 --> 00:59:05,294
-You two look great together.
-I'm so happy for you.

663
00:59:05,378 --> 00:59:06,671
Congratulations.

664
00:59:06,754 --> 00:59:08,130
-Congratulations.
-Congratulations.

665
00:59:08,214 --> 00:59:09,131
Congratulations.

666
00:59:09,215 --> 00:59:11,133
-I'll bring out some more wine.
-All right.

667
00:59:13,970 --> 00:59:15,054
Cheers.

668
00:59:22,103 --> 00:59:23,396
You're here just in time.

669
00:59:23,479 --> 00:59:25,314
Your dad announced
they're getting married.

670
00:59:25,398 --> 00:59:26,649
You should congratulate them.

671
00:59:50,214 --> 00:59:51,424
What about the Unit 610 guy?

672
00:59:52,633 --> 00:59:53,884
It took you long enough to ask.

673
00:59:55,011 --> 00:59:56,262
I'll end things with him.

674
00:59:56,345 --> 00:59:57,763
You're only ending it now?

675
00:59:58,931 --> 01:00:00,808
Seon-gyu knows everything.

676
01:00:01,726 --> 01:00:04,103
He said he'd tell me
once he figured things out,

677
01:00:04,186 --> 01:00:05,896
so I hadn't been able to end things.

678
01:00:08,065 --> 01:00:08,899
Eun-a.

679
01:00:08,983 --> 01:00:13,654
Love doesn't happen in perfect order.

680
01:00:13,738 --> 01:00:15,906
No wonder why
you always have a guy around.

681
01:00:15,990 --> 01:00:17,325
There's never a break with you.

682
01:00:17,408 --> 01:00:19,368
-Watch what you say.
-You watch it.

683
01:00:19,452 --> 01:00:20,953
How dare you two-time my dad?

684
01:00:25,333 --> 01:00:27,001
Seon-gyu is the one I have feelings for.

685
01:00:27,084 --> 01:00:28,628
The one in Unit 610 knows that too.

686
01:00:28,711 --> 01:00:31,339
I've never deceived or misled anyone.

687
01:00:31,422 --> 01:00:33,716
So you're saying you'll live
however you want

688
01:00:33,799 --> 01:00:35,718
and everyone else
has to just deal with it?

689
01:00:36,927 --> 01:00:39,055
And my dad just accepted that nonsense?

690
01:00:41,682 --> 01:00:43,184
What do you take my dad for?

691
01:00:44,226 --> 01:00:46,812
He's a good person, but someone like you…

692
01:00:46,896 --> 01:00:47,813
This is the last time.

693
01:00:47,897 --> 01:00:49,815
I'll let your insults slide today,

694
01:00:49,899 --> 01:00:51,150
but after this,

695
01:00:51,942 --> 01:00:53,110
not a chance.

696
01:00:58,449 --> 01:00:59,283
Mo Eun-a.

697
01:01:02,244 --> 01:01:03,287
Mo Eun-a!

698
01:01:04,205 --> 01:01:05,039
Let go.

699
01:01:05,956 --> 01:01:07,249
You should congratulate them.

700
01:01:07,333 --> 01:01:09,085
You're startling our guests.

701
01:01:09,168 --> 01:01:10,628
Take this and go back inside.

702
01:01:10,711 --> 01:01:12,463
You're so damn good at your job.

703
01:01:16,759 --> 01:01:20,137
Aren't you a little old to be so worked up
over your dad's relationship?

704
01:01:21,305 --> 01:01:23,015
You should focus on your own life.

705
01:01:24,684 --> 01:01:25,851
I'll try to find you a job.

706
01:01:28,729 --> 01:01:30,106
I can't promise it'll help though.

707
01:02:27,913 --> 01:02:30,666
It tends to stop or flip over
on steep inclines.

708
01:02:31,584 --> 01:02:33,461
Could the weight distribution be off?

709
01:02:33,544 --> 01:02:35,379
How about switching to a two-wheel design?

710
01:02:35,463 --> 01:02:36,881
<i>Are you busy?</i>

711
01:02:36,964 --> 01:02:38,174
<i>I'm in my professor's lab.</i>

712
01:02:38,257 --> 01:02:40,134
<i>It's only for grad students,</i>

713
01:02:40,217 --> 01:02:42,511
<i>but the TA let me in,</i>
<i>so it's my first time here.</i>

714
01:02:42,595 --> 01:02:43,554
<i>It's pretty cool.</i>

715
01:02:44,138 --> 01:02:46,932
<i>You sound busy. What time do you finish?</i>

716
01:02:47,016 --> 01:02:50,603
<i>What is it? If it's urgent,</i>
<i>I can call you right now.</i>

717
01:02:50,686 --> 01:02:52,938
You should be majoring in flattery.

718
01:02:53,939 --> 01:02:56,233
Honestly. We'll continue this in a bit.

719
01:02:56,317 --> 01:02:58,736
<i>-Never mind. I'll catch you later.</i>
-Yes, Professor.

720
01:02:59,487 --> 01:03:01,906
The professor likes supreme pizza.

721
01:03:01,989 --> 01:03:04,200
-Could I go use the restroom?
-Yeah, sure.

722
01:03:05,534 --> 01:03:06,827
Professor, please have some.

723
01:03:11,040 --> 01:03:12,500
<i>Did you know?</i>

724
01:03:13,000 --> 01:03:16,462
<i>Apparently, you can see Namsan</i>
<i>from anywhere in Seoul.</i>

725
01:03:16,545 --> 01:03:19,882
<i>So from now on, your name is Namsan.</i>

726
01:03:19,965 --> 01:03:21,175
<i>Yeon Namsan.</i>

727
01:03:23,636 --> 01:03:26,931
<i>I guess I'm still stuck in uncertainty.</i>

728
01:03:35,523 --> 01:03:36,607
<i>Where are you?</i>

729
01:03:37,691 --> 01:03:39,068
<i>The wetlands.</i>

730
01:03:39,151 --> 01:03:42,279
<i>No. I'm actually at the bus stop now.</i>

731
01:03:45,950 --> 01:03:48,786
TAE-SEO

732
01:03:55,292 --> 01:03:56,252
<i>You're in Seoul, right?</i>

733
01:03:57,878 --> 01:04:00,172
<i>While I was wandering,</i>
<i>I was going to buy some makeup</i>

734
01:04:00,256 --> 01:04:02,466
<i>and get a bowl of noodles.</i>

735
01:04:03,175 --> 01:04:05,052
<i>You have important things going on.</i>

736
01:04:05,135 --> 01:04:06,554
<i>Don't waste your time.</i>

737
01:04:06,637 --> 01:04:09,640
<i>I have plenty of time,</i>
<i>so I'll drop by again.</i>

738
01:04:10,558 --> 01:04:12,309
<i>Don't be ridiculous.</i>

739
01:04:12,393 --> 01:04:14,311
<i>Nothing matters more</i>
<i>than us being together.</i>

740
01:04:21,110 --> 01:04:24,446
<i>Tae-seo, I really want to see you.</i>

741
01:04:31,287 --> 01:04:32,246
<i>I'm on my way.</i>

742
01:04:33,080 --> 01:04:34,415
<i>You don't know where I am.</i>

743
01:04:35,791 --> 01:04:36,625
<i>Hang on.</i>

744
01:04:44,800 --> 01:04:45,968
<i>I have one more stop.</i>

745
01:04:46,051 --> 01:04:46,886
<i>I'm almost there.</i>

746
01:04:58,856 --> 01:05:00,316
GANGBYEON STATION

747
01:05:10,659 --> 01:05:13,829
<i>I can hear Yeon Tae-seo coming.</i>

748
01:05:24,506 --> 01:05:26,300
<i>I'm done wandering.</i>

749
01:05:29,303 --> 01:05:32,222
STILL SHINING

750
01:05:58,165 --> 01:06:01,085
<i>You were really going through it</i>
<i>before you did your military duty.</i>

751
01:06:01,794 --> 01:06:03,337
<i>I hate goodbyes.</i>

752
01:06:04,254 --> 01:06:05,756
For 10 years, I'd forgotten.

753
01:06:06,966 --> 01:06:08,300
<i>They were gone.</i>

754
01:06:08,384 --> 01:06:10,094
Eun-a…

755
01:06:10,177 --> 01:06:12,054
You haven't heard from her, have you?

756
01:06:12,763 --> 01:06:13,973
<i>Let's stop…</i>

757
01:06:15,265 --> 01:06:17,059
<i>with the worries and everything else.</i>

758
01:06:17,142 --> 01:06:18,352
<i>I thought of you.</i>

759
01:06:21,563 --> 01:06:24,274
<i>I had hoped to see you at least once.</i>

760
01:06:31,323 --> 01:06:33,325
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee
